{"key":"post-13696226","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13696226</id>\n<content>Straw can be obtained from any animal feed store.&amp;nbsp; You'll have to shred it yourself.&amp;nbsp; Put about six inches of dry straw in the bottom of a 55 gallon drum and go at it with a weed whacker until it's the size you want.&amp;nbsp; Repeat until you have enough.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There's exemptions in the organic certification standards to allow one to use non-organic substrates if certified organic ones are not commercially available, but I've yet to avail myself of that loophole.&amp;nbsp; I'm using sawdust that has been certified organic to grow my shiitake.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13696234</next>\n<prev>13696215</prev>\n<first>13696047</first>\n<last>13696540</last>\n<when>1293570350</when>\n<utime>12/28/10 11:05 PM</utime>\n</post>"}